      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "South Carolina\n\nUnto the Worthy Gentlemen Members of the St. Andrews Club assembled at their annual Anniversary 30th November 1769\n\nThe Petition of John Graham of Charlestown - a Native of Scotland - \n\nMost Humbly Sheweth\n\nThat you petitioner has resided in this province for a considerable space of time and having met with considerable success by trade and otherways, are now reduced in his old age without any employ or calling, adequate to acquire even the comforts of life, your petitioner therefore humbly submits his deplorable circumstances into your known humanity, and your petitioner would only crave your generous assistance for any small pittance in order to put your petitioner in a small comfortable manner.\n\nMay it therefore please you to take your humble petitioner's case into your most serious consideration and be pleased to grant such relief as to you may seem meet. And your petitioner is in duty ever bound to pray etc...\n\n[Petitioner's signature] John Graham Snr\n\nCharles Town\n26th Novemr 1769"
    },
